Nov 26 2009 	Recently rennovated best location	Date : 25.11.2009We have just returned from a 5 days stay at the Dream Palace Hotel. The hotel is magnificent with fresh interiors, nice and clean bed linens, towels etc. &amp; very good bathrooms. We stayed on 5th Floor in Deluxe double room, which has different scheme from other floors. We were just expecting a few nibbles but breakfast is a lovely continental spread with cheeses fruits, cakes, Arab breads etc. The location of the hotel is in Deira Dubai, which is old Dubai. Right around the hotel there are two good Malls, many super stores, good restaurants only 3-5 minutes walking distance. Gold Souk is also quite near, 10-15 minutes by taxi ( there is always traffic Jam when you go towards that area)There is nearby metro station on Al Rigga road from where you have options to go to new Dubai, Mall of emirates, Airport by paying merely 6-9 dirham.The hotel staff is very co-operative and courtious. I needed an adopter for my camera charger, which was arranged within a short time. My return flight back was scheduled at 22:40,but hotel people allowed me to stay in the hotel upto 18:00 without any extra charges. However the hotel transport from and to airport was through an old bus without curtain, which posed a problem during day time when the sun was at its peak on our way from airport to hotel. Since the distance of airport from the hotel is not much, the hotel could have arranged a car. Overall I would say this is probably the best hotel in 3 star category we have ever stayed in on holiday. YASHPALNEW DELHIINDIA	
Nov 1 2009 	Nice and Cosy	Dream palace hotel was really nice and cosy place to stay, i did my booking online through www.booking.com and got a single room for great price exclusive of taxes but if u compare dubai, that tax money was peanut. Its located in good area with great food joints around, i did not try the hotel restaurants. I reached dubai on 31st oct, took metro from terminal 3 to AL-RIGGA station, n just walked to the hotel (around 10 mins)(u can ask people for direction to AL-MURAQBAT road. Host at reception was nice and helpful (dont expect it to be a 7 seven hotel). Room was small but cosy and very clean. No free internet (10dhs for an hour), but managed somehow, rest all mery mery, n good, Over all i can give it 7.5 of 10	
