Sep 20 2009 	A inexpensive Palace	Received a recomendation to stay at the Dream Palace from my co-workers.I was very impressed. First, I paid about $40 (w/out breakfast) for the room. The roomwas clean, modern and with a flat-screen TV. The bathroom was modern with a glass shower and completly updated. The staff even let me use the internet in the lobby for about 10 minutes without an additional payment. A small pool and jacuzzi on the roof. The gym is very basic, but has 1 or 2 treadmills. There is even a sauna...very nice after a long day on the town.I travel through Dubai frequently, sometimes with a company paid hotel (which the Dream Palace is not on their list..it should be). When I have to pay for a hotel, this is definitley the one I would stay at. For $40 a night in Dubai, I can afford the dream in this expensive city!	
