Jul 6 2009 	Newly renowated good value for money	The hotel is newly renowated, rooms are nice and quite big. The view isn't spectacular but at all it is a very good offer in resonable price. We didn't have a breakfast and possibly this hotel doesn't offer them. We booked with otel.com what is good site for booking in Dubai as you pay full price and don't have to be worried about additionaly paid 10% local tax. The photos on otel are old as well so the hotel looks much beter tha there. The hotel is in Deira district not that far from center but you have to either take a taxi for about 4-5USD or bus to Deira center, It is not that close to the airport as well (25-30min). Comparing to other hotels in Dubai (and references on tripadvisor) there is no any disco closeby. It is nice and quiet.	
Jul 6 2009 	Excellent value better than expected	We reserved here based on the TripAdvisor reviews, and we were pleasantly surprised. The hotel was recently renovated, so everything is clean and new-looking. We reserved it at the airport's Central Reservation Service, no problem at all. Location is near the Reef Mall. It is not far from the airport as the crow flies, but the roadway design means it is twice as far coming from the airport as going To the airport! Rooftop swimming pool is small, like a bathtub in the incredible summer heat; but still very pleasant and clean. Overall, basic hotel, quite comfortable and quiet, though not a luxury resort. Also note that it is near a couple of good barbers and restaurants!	
