Jun 12 2009 	totally ok for the price positively surprised	I've stayed in a number of budget hotels and hostels, but this one was really nice, much more than I had expected. not exactly a &quot;palace&quot;, but a nice hotel. friendly staff, the room was nice, bathroom very bright (mine even had a window) which I like. Although they had a sign up that they are doing construction work, I didn't hear any of it. The restaurant was quite ok as well (not licensed), and there are plenty of other places to eat around the hotel and in the mall right beside it. getting to some of Dubai's attractions is a bit of a ride (also the hop on hop off bus stop is a short ride/long walk in the heat away), but from the idea I got, there is no perfect location in Dubai (at least until the metro is finished). They have a pool up on the roof (and gym and sauna), but the water didn't look too clean to me, so I didn't go in.	
