Mar 18 2009 	Dream Palace OK 4 place to sleep	Nice location not far from the city center. Reasonable rates. Family hotel, meaning no alcohol / discos and no visitors to guest rooms. If a friend from outside visits, you have to meet in the lobby. Quiet, fairly clean. Was interested only in a decent place to sleep at night, as I was attending a 3-day conference in a nearby, more expensive hotel. So, I didn't check out any of the amenities. Would be quite comfortable taking family with me next time for an overnight stay.	
Feb 28 2009 	Probably the crappiest hotel in Dubai	My husband and I stayed one night at Dream Palace because we needed to stay in Dubai for a night after our vacation in Fujairah in order to catch our plane out the next day. The place was horrible. It smelled seriously weird and the rooms were frightful. I figured it wouldn't be a big deal since we were only staying for a night, but you can pay a tiny bit more and probably get something (anything) nicer than this place. The front desk was always overwhelmed, so we had to sit on our suitcases in the cramped lobby while we waited for them to check the guests in. They really need to get a better handle on the check-in process. On the bright side, it's a short taxi ride to City Center Mall. If you're absolutely desperate and on a tight budget, the you'll probably be ok. But if you're sensitive to bad smells and easily infuriated by bad service, go someplace else!	
Jan 22 2009 	Ok if you just need a clean efficient place to stay over	Booked this place through Expedia for my trip through Dubai to Afghanistan. I got the room for about $95 for an evening, which wasn't bad for what I got. Taxi ride was about $10 there and about a 10-15 minute ride depending on the traffic. Make sure you have the address of the hotel with you so the driver can find it quickly, and probably the phone number there as well. The front desk was very polite and easy to understand that evening. The porter was very very helpful and nice. The place is very clean for being an older hotel. The room was clean and efficient for what I was looking for; the bathroom was the biggest issue. Very small! Otherwise, had a movie channel and the BBC to watch, and ordered some food that evening which was not expensive and very good. The morning consisted of having the buffet breakfast, which was adequate. Nothing terrible on it, but nothing special. It was excellent for the price. If you need a ride back to the hotel, the van runs about every four hours. You have to pay for the internet too; not too expensive and they have computers downstairs or wireless. Overall, the staff was very friendly, and I would stay there again if I go through again.	
